1
00:00:51,259 --> 00:00:53,928
{\an8}You still believe Chiara is innocent.

2
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:57,348
{\an8}<i>That she isn't part</i>
<i>of her family's criminal syndicate.</i>

3
00:00:57,432 --> 00:01:01,895
{\an8}I will finish him myself!

4
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:04,647
{\an8}The truth is right in front of you.
What are you waiting for?

5
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:06,566
{\an8}<i>I don't care who Chiara is.</i>

6
00:01:06,649 --> 00:01:07,942
{\an8}Because I love her.

7
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:10,487
{\an8}I love her very much.

8
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:21,122
{\an8}Dad… Dad, we need to leave.

9
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:22,916
{\an8}You need to go back to Cebu first.

10
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:24,542
{\an8}Did something happen?

11
00:01:24,626 --> 00:01:26,169
{\an8}The Moravianos.

12
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:28,505
{\an8}The Valtrovis, Dad.

13
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:29,798
{\an8}They know now.

14
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:34,010
{\an8}They already know
that I'm working for the police.

15
00:01:35,637 --> 00:01:37,514
{\an8}I'm sure you'll be their next target.

16
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:39,516
{\an8}Yes.

17
00:01:39,599 --> 00:01:41,643
{\an8}That's why we need to leave immediately.

18
00:01:41,726 --> 00:01:44,729
{\an8}Dad… You need to take Mom
back to Cebu first.

19
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:45,730
{\an8}What about you?

20
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:49,400
{\an8}I'll take care of myself.

21
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:51,194
{\an8}The protocol has already
been explained to me

22
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:53,238
{\an8}for situations like this.

23
00:01:56,658 --> 00:01:59,536
{\an8}You know, it's a good thing the burger
and extra fries showed up when they did.

24
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:01,621
{\an8}The timing was just perfect.

25
00:02:01,704 --> 00:02:04,624
{\an8}Cocoy won't be the only one
trying to kill you.

26
00:02:04,707 --> 00:02:08,628
{\an8}And there won't always be
a burger and fries around to save you.

27
00:02:08,711 --> 00:02:09,587
{\an8}I understand that.

28
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:11,756
{\an8}That's why I'll be more careful, okay?

29
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:13,383
{\an8}Promise.

30
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:15,802
{\an8}Being careful isn't enough, Mikoy.

31
00:02:15,885 --> 00:02:17,804
{\an8}You have to prepare for the worst.

32
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:19,222
{\an8}The worst?

33
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:22,600
{\an8}- Like what?
- Like when your cover gets blown.

34
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:26,104
{\an8}- You mean burned?
- Yes. Burned.

35
00:02:26,187 --> 00:02:29,065
{\an8}It means the Moravianos
have discovered your identity,

36
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:31,609
{\an8}and they know you're an agency asset.

37
00:02:32,861 --> 00:02:34,529
{\an8}What do I do if that happens?

38
00:02:34,612 --> 00:02:37,490
{\an8}You need to upgrade your burger and fries.

39
00:02:37,574 --> 00:02:39,159
{\an8}You need a grande now.

40
00:02:39,742 --> 00:02:42,287
{\an8}Grande? What grande?

41
00:02:42,871 --> 00:02:45,498
{\an8}<i>You can check into any hotel</i>
<i>in Metro Manila</i>

42
00:02:45,582 --> 00:02:47,458
{\an8}<i>under the name Grande.</i>

43
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:48,793
{\an8}Room for one.

44
00:02:48,877 --> 00:02:50,461
{\an8}Under Alexander Grande.

45
00:02:50,545 --> 00:02:52,130
{\an8}We have Grande here. Prepare the room.

46
00:02:54,757 --> 00:02:56,092
{\an8}Dad…

47
00:02:56,175 --> 00:02:57,552
{\an8}I'll be okay.

48
00:02:58,928 --> 00:03:00,388
{\an8}They'll provide me protection.

49
00:03:00,471 --> 00:03:01,556
{\an8}They should.

50
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:03,474
Dad.

51
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:05,727
You need to get away first.

52
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:09,355
Because I'm sure you'll be next.

53
00:03:12,233 --> 00:03:13,359
Okay.

54
00:03:14,652 --> 00:03:16,738
I'll take care of your mother and brother.

55
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:20,074
So make sure you stay safe.

56
00:03:23,369 --> 00:03:24,495
Dad, I'm sorry.

57
00:03:25,288 --> 00:03:26,581
I've dragged you into this.

58
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:29,334
I never thought it would come to this.

59
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:32,545
At first, I thought I was helping, but…

60
00:03:35,965 --> 00:03:36,841
Mikoy.

61
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,344
I told you before.

62
00:03:39,427 --> 00:03:41,471
We're a complicated family.

63
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:43,806
But we're still family.

64
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:46,559
We don't give up on each other.

65
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:48,811
No matter what happens,

66
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:53,358
we're on the same side, so there's
no reason for you to feel guilty.

67
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:07,413
How sweet, father and son
are hugging each other.

68
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,666
Even in this heat. What are you doing?

69
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:12,001
Let me join too, please.

70
00:05:35,209 --> 00:05:36,252
Bok!

71
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:39,255
Bok, what are you doing?

72
00:05:39,338 --> 00:05:41,382
Come on. Get back here.

73
00:05:41,466 --> 00:05:44,218
- What are you doing?
- I need to leave. Let me go.

74
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:47,388
Bok, how are you going to leave? Huh?

75
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:50,391
You are in no shape to move. Bok.

76
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:53,061
Bok, so many-- You have so many wounds.

77
00:05:53,144 --> 00:05:54,395
You're covered in bandages.

78
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:56,105
So how are you going to leave?

79
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:57,857
I can still move.

80
00:05:57,940 --> 00:05:59,734
These wounds are nothing.

81
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:02,737
Okay, I understand.

82
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:04,489
But fine, let's make a deal.

83
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:06,365
Just recover first,
then I'll let you leave.

84
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:07,450
I'll even treat you.

85
00:06:07,533 --> 00:06:08,534
Bok, come on.

86
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:11,204
I need to get to Mikoy.
His life is in danger.

87
00:06:11,287 --> 00:06:12,705
Enough already.

88
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,332
It's always Mikoy.

89
00:06:14,415 --> 00:06:16,751
You never talk about
anything else but Mikoy.

90
00:06:16,834 --> 00:06:19,337
Now what? What happened to us? Huh?

91
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:21,547
Is that really how it is?

92
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:23,883
You're willing to die just for Mikoy?

93
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:28,596
He's important to the case
we're building against the Moravianos.

94
00:06:29,388 --> 00:06:32,100
If that's the risk
I need to take, I'll take that.

95
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:33,851
Sianong, he's our asset.

96
00:06:33,935 --> 00:06:35,978
And he is now our liability.

97
00:06:36,062 --> 00:06:37,772
Can't you see that?

98
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:40,066
We need to get rid of him cleanly.

99
00:06:40,149 --> 00:06:41,609
While we still have time.

100
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:44,070
While we still have a chance.

101
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:47,698
What do you mean?

102
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:54,831
Sianong, what did you do?

103
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:05,883
Well, we need to leave.

104
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:08,177
I've already bought tickets to Cebu.

105
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:09,929
You mean right now?

106
00:07:10,012 --> 00:07:11,472
Why so suddenly?

107
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:13,808
You know what people say.

108
00:07:13,891 --> 00:07:15,184
The view is beautiful.

109
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:16,644
Everything from…

110
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:19,272
from up there, there are moons and stars.

111
00:07:19,355 --> 00:07:21,399
To make things a little romantic.

112
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:23,693
Stop fooling around with me.

113
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:25,653
What moon and stars are you talking about?

114
00:07:25,736 --> 00:07:27,405
They're in outer space.

115
00:07:27,488 --> 00:07:29,407
Besides, the pollution here
in the Philippines is so bad,

116
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:31,617
I can't even see those stars and moon.

117
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:35,621
Okay, so we won't have to wait
in a long line at the airport.

118
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,500
Tell me.

119
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,711
Is something bad happening?

120
00:07:42,378 --> 00:07:45,339
Tell me. Is there something
I need to know?

121
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:47,467
Why would you think that?

122
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:48,468
How?

123
00:07:48,551 --> 00:07:50,636
Honey, you're overthinking.

124
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:53,014
Let's just pack our things. Come on.

125
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:55,683
Where's Mikoy?

126
00:07:55,766 --> 00:07:57,143
Tell me. Where's Mikoy?

127
00:07:57,226 --> 00:08:00,855
He had something to take care of,
and he might be gone for a while. Okay?

128
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:04,025
We'll just call him once we land in Cebu.

129
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:06,235
Oh, Mario Pinagpala, you know,

130
00:08:06,319 --> 00:08:09,447
you may be blessed,
but you're not very good at lying.

131
00:08:09,530 --> 00:08:11,449
Do you think I don't notice those

132
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:13,451
knowing looks between you and Mikoy.

133
00:08:13,534 --> 00:08:15,912
The way you look at each other.

134
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:17,371
When are you going to tell me the truth?

135
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:19,040
Okay, look.

136
00:08:19,123 --> 00:08:21,250
I'll tell you everything.

137
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:23,794
But… not this time.

138
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:26,214
We need to leave.

139
00:08:28,424 --> 00:08:29,634
Trust me.

140
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:34,388
Come on, let's go. Hurry up.

141
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:36,516
You're making me panic.

142
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:40,686
That's what you did?

143
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:43,439
You think Mikoy will betray us?

144
00:08:44,190 --> 00:08:45,107
Bok.

145
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,945
I don't know if you're thinking
straight right now,. Sorry.

146
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:51,113
But isn't it obvious?

147
00:08:52,156 --> 00:08:54,283
He fed us that fake intel.

148
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:56,160
What other reason could there be?

149
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:59,497
To throw us off
this investigation. That's it.

150
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:00,581
But haven't you realized

151
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:03,042
that it could have been
planted intelligence?

152
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:05,419
Exactly. Planted intelligence.

153
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:06,754
And for Viktor to do that,

154
00:09:06,837 --> 00:09:08,631
it means he's been watching
for a long time.

155
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:10,591
He's suspected Mikoy for a long time.

156
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:12,260
Why can't you see that?

157
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:14,345
Looks like it's been a long time indeed.

158
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:17,682
Maybe it started when Viktor
assigned Carlota

159
00:09:17,765 --> 00:09:19,392
as Mikoy's secretary,

160
00:09:19,475 --> 00:09:20,851
and Mikoy never noticed

161
00:09:20,935 --> 00:09:23,729
because he isn't trained to spot it.

162
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:25,356
Isn't that possible?

163
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:28,776
Fine.

164
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,530
Let's say you're right, okay?

165
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:36,492
That means we're also
responsible for this because

166
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:37,994
we failed to see it.

167
00:09:38,077 --> 00:09:40,538
We are agents. We are trained for this.

168
00:09:40,621 --> 00:09:41,539
Fine.

169
00:09:43,457 --> 00:09:45,459
Bok, lie back down.

170
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:47,295
Exactly.

171
00:09:47,378 --> 00:09:50,298
Even us agents make mistakes, Sianong.

172
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:53,301
What more Mikoy, who's just a civilian?

173
00:09:54,635 --> 00:09:57,847
And now his life is in danger
because Viktor wants him dead.

174
00:09:59,807 --> 00:10:00,766
No.

175
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:03,686
I don't think Viktor will kill him.

176
00:10:03,769 --> 00:10:07,523
Because if he really wanted to kill Mikoy,
he would've done it a long time ago.

177
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:08,983
He should have done it already.

178
00:10:09,066 --> 00:10:10,568
Knowing Viktor, he can kill anyone,

179
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:12,695
especially people who betray him.

180
00:10:12,778 --> 00:10:17,366
But with Mikoy, somehow,
he made efforts to keep him alive.

181
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,747
And there's only one reason for that.

182
00:10:24,373 --> 00:10:25,291
Chiara.

183
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:28,419
I think Chiara is trying to protect him.

184
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:29,420
Yes.

185
00:10:32,131 --> 00:10:33,382
Either that

186
00:10:34,675 --> 00:10:37,428
or maybe Chiara wants to kill him herself.

187
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:55,131
<i>It's more than just good.</i>

188
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:57,091
The cleanup has started.

189
00:11:57,633 --> 00:12:00,886
And you'll be delighted to know
who initiated the attack.

190
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:06,684
I have now unleashed
our most dangerous weapon.

191
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:34,772
Hey! Idiot!

192
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:37,441
You should have your license revoked.

193
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:46,033
Hey! You devil.

194
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:54,625
Looks like you're hard to surprise.

195
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:56,585
I was trying to surprise you.

196
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:58,587
But it seems you have eyes
at the back of your head.

197
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:03,717
Your hobby?

198
00:14:04,426 --> 00:14:06,345
Because I'm good at that too.

199
00:14:07,972 --> 00:14:09,890
Oh. Stabbing?

200
00:14:09,974 --> 00:14:11,267
No.

201
00:14:12,017 --> 00:14:13,102
Backstabbing.

202
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:19,358
I know what you're doing.

203
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,987
I just want you to know
it's not working on me.

204
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,627
You want some? Here you go.

205
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:27,760
There!

206
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:31,096
Eat my smoke, idiot.

207
00:15:32,556 --> 00:15:35,100
These reckless riders. They're everywhere.

208
00:15:35,184 --> 00:15:36,435
What is it, harvest season?

209
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:45,110
Hey! Hey!

210
00:15:57,831 --> 00:15:59,208
Hey!

211
00:16:03,420 --> 00:16:05,089
What's this guy's problem?

212
00:16:05,172 --> 00:16:07,049
I think he's messing with me.

213
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:18,811
Fight to stay alive,
even if you have to crawl.

214
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:21,230
Don't let go. Don't give up.

215
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:23,232
Because there's one thing
I can promise you.

216
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:25,401
Help will always come for you.

217
00:17:02,563 --> 00:17:05,733
I won't stop you anymore.
I'll even back you up.

218
00:17:05,816 --> 00:17:07,735
Sianong, you know me.

219
00:17:07,818 --> 00:17:10,195
I don't back down from a fight.

220
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,912
- Sir.
- What's this?

221
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:21,165
Why is she dressed already?

222
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:26,128
We need to secure Mikoy.
His life is in danger.

223
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:28,922
Viktor already knows he's working for us.

224
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:32,718
And at this moment, he may have
already sent someone to kill Mikoy.

225
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:37,347
That was my plan, too.

226
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:40,100
That's why I'm here to tell you

227
00:17:40,934 --> 00:17:42,561
not to worry about him.

228
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,441
What kind of help?

229
00:17:47,524 --> 00:17:49,151
I've already talked to Mikoy.

230
00:17:49,234 --> 00:17:51,153
I told him about our backup plan.

231
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:53,572
He's on his way to a nearby hotel.

232
00:17:53,655 --> 00:17:55,783
To explore our Grande option.

233
00:17:55,866 --> 00:17:57,367
That's good then.

234
00:17:58,035 --> 00:17:59,912
We have information on his location.

235
00:17:59,995 --> 00:18:01,955
So now, we can secure him better.

236
00:18:02,039 --> 00:18:04,958
We can transfer him
to our nearest safe house.

237
00:18:05,626 --> 00:18:06,627
Right?

238
00:18:08,921 --> 00:18:10,881
That's a great suggestion.

239
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:17,971
But you have a lot of explaining to do.

240
00:18:19,014 --> 00:18:20,224
A lot!

241
00:19:11,942 --> 00:19:14,653
<i>She is the Valtrovi's secret assassin.</i>

242
00:19:14,736 --> 00:19:15,779
<i>She is La Fornarina.</i>

243
00:19:23,620 --> 00:19:24,788
Sweetheart!

244
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:28,250
Aren't you happy to see me?

245
00:19:31,461 --> 00:19:32,671
It's Mikoy.

246
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:36,008
Mikoy? Where are you?

247
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:38,510
Hello? Agent Alex? How are you?

248
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:40,137
<i>But wait, that can wait.</i>

249
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:41,471
I actually need your help.

250
00:19:41,555 --> 00:19:42,681
Sweetheart!

251
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:45,726
Wait, was that a gunshot?

252
00:19:45,809 --> 00:19:47,644
Are you in a gunfire situation?

253
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:48,770
Looks like it.

254
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:50,856
And yes, those are real bullets.

255
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:53,400
Sorry, I wasn't able to make it
to our Grande plan.

256
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:57,988
- Because I was followed.
- By who?

257
00:19:59,573 --> 00:20:00,699
La Fornarina!

258
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:03,619
Wait a second. Let me show you. Here.

259
00:20:05,579 --> 00:20:07,331
- There she is!
- Mikoy!

260
00:20:15,589 --> 00:20:17,925
Mikoy? Mikoy?

261
00:20:35,234 --> 00:20:36,526
- <i>I need to find Mikoy.</i>
- Agent Dara, track Mikoy now.

262
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:37,736
I'm on it, Agent Sianong.

263
00:20:38,779 --> 00:20:40,197
We're running out of time.

264
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:41,281
I said I'm on it.

265
00:20:43,825 --> 00:20:45,744
Bok, this is exactly
what I've been telling you.

266
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:48,747
Can we please just stay
in the hospital. You?

267
00:20:49,581 --> 00:20:51,375
I'll handle Mikoy. I'll take care of him.

268
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:52,960
I'll update you when it's over.

269
00:20:53,543 --> 00:20:55,170
- Really?
- Yes.

270
00:20:55,254 --> 00:20:57,547
Just a while ago, you looked like
you wanted to terminate him

271
00:20:57,631 --> 00:20:59,258
like he was a disposable cup.

272
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:02,094
Okay, fine. Sorry.

273
00:21:02,177 --> 00:21:03,720
Okay now, Bok?

274
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:06,723
Let me handle Mikoy.
I'll take care of him.

275
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:09,226
I'll keep you updated
from time to time. I promise.

276
00:21:09,309 --> 00:21:11,228
How can you take care of him

277
00:21:11,937 --> 00:21:14,231
when you were the first one
who didn't trust him?

278
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:17,901
Bok, I'm not blaming you,

279
00:21:17,985 --> 00:21:20,445
but trust is the foundation
of our relationship

280
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:22,155
with all of our assets.

281
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:23,657
Including Mikoy.

282
00:21:23,740 --> 00:21:25,367
And I hope this serves as a lesson.

283
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:29,413
You need to trust people
if you want them to trust you.

284
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:32,958
And Mikoy is putting all his trust in us.

285
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:35,168
So we should do the same for him.

286
00:21:35,961 --> 00:21:38,422
Okay.

287
00:21:38,505 --> 00:21:39,589
I'll make it up to him, okay?

288
00:21:39,673 --> 00:21:41,091
I'll make it up to him, guys.

289
00:21:41,842 --> 00:21:43,176
What's Mikoy's last known location?

290
00:21:43,260 --> 00:21:44,511
We lost his phone signal.

291
00:21:44,594 --> 00:21:47,639
But I intercepted a tip
about a shoot-out along Mapayapa Road.

292
00:21:47,723 --> 00:21:49,599
Okay, good. Let's move.

293
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:51,935
Careful.

294
00:22:07,784 --> 00:22:09,494
No, no, no.

295
00:22:39,149 --> 00:22:41,818
Well… Start gathering

296
00:22:41,902 --> 00:22:43,779
what crashed there.

297
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:46,615
We need to secure our own footage.

298
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:48,950
Global Agency for Government Operations.

299
00:22:49,034 --> 00:22:50,410
We're only here to investigate.

300
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:54,164
The GAGO has no jurisdiction
over this matter--

301
00:22:54,247 --> 00:22:56,875
Sir, there is an ongoing
national security operation,

302
00:22:57,375 --> 00:22:59,711
and the syndicates we've been monitoring

303
00:22:59,795 --> 00:23:00,796
appear to be connected to this.

304
00:23:00,879 --> 00:23:02,130
Even so,

305
00:23:02,756 --> 00:23:03,882
this is our crime scene--

306
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:06,927
This isn't just
a simple road rage case, sir.

307
00:23:07,010 --> 00:23:09,304
And we'd like to reach them
while they're still alive.

308
00:23:09,387 --> 00:23:11,723
Let's not turn this
into one of those shows

309
00:23:11,807 --> 00:23:13,767
where the police arrive late and then

310
00:23:13,850 --> 00:23:16,520
end up serving as nothing more
than the cleanup crew

311
00:23:17,104 --> 00:23:19,856
and at the same time,
just take pictures at the crime scene.

312
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:21,483
No. Even so, sir,

313
00:23:21,566 --> 00:23:23,568
- it's still our--
- And if something goes wrong

314
00:23:23,652 --> 00:23:27,030
because we're arguing here
about whose jurisdiction this is,

315
00:23:28,156 --> 00:23:29,407
we'll both be in trouble.

316
00:24:21,376 --> 00:24:24,296
There are still gunshots
near the grocery store around here.

317
00:24:24,379 --> 00:24:26,131
I think it's still Chiara.

318
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:30,886
Hey! Bok!

319
00:24:34,890 --> 00:24:37,184
Is there nothing we can do?
Nothing at all, Viktor?

320
00:24:52,407 --> 00:24:54,492
Maybe you never really knew me.

